5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to screen-based instruction; to require the
10 State Board of Education to establish standards for
11 screen-based instruction in kindergarten through twelfth
12 grade; to create the Instructional Technology Task Force
13 within the State Department of Education; to require the
14 standards to reflect the recommendations of the task force;
15 and to provide certain exceptions from any prohibitions on
16 screen-use.
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
18 Section 1. The Legislature finds and declares the
19 following:
20 (1) Early elementary years are critical for children's
21 brain development, literacy acquisition, attention formation,
22 and executive function.
23 (2) Research demonstrates that children learn
24 foundation skills most effectively through direct instruction,
25 handwriting, physical texts, manipulatives, and sustained
26 interaction with teachers and peers.
27 (3) Educational technology is most effective when used
28 intentionally and in moderation and should not displace
Page 1

intentionally and in moderation and should not displace
