85 instruction standards on students, such as the average daily
86 screen time use per student. The board shall provide a copy of
87 the progress report for the preceding academic year to the
88 Governor and the Legislature no later than October 1 of each
89 year.
90 (d) The department shall oversee compliance with this
91 act and may adopt rules necessary to enforce compliance.
92 Section 4. (a)(1) The Instructional Technology Task
93 Force is created within the department. The membership of the
94 task force shall be composed of the following:
95 a. Each of the following, appointed by the Governor:
96 1. Four classroom teachers, including two elementary
97 school teachers, one middle school teacher, and one high
98 school teacher.
99 2. One parent of a public school student.
100 3. One pediatric ophthalmologist or vision health
101 specialist.
102 b. Two nationally recognized experts in child
103 development, pediatric digital media research, or cognitive
104 science, one of whom shall be appointed by the President Pro
105 Tempore of the Senate and one of whom shall be appointed by
106 the Speaker of the House of Representatives.
107 c. Two literacy or childhood development experts, one
108 of whom shall specialize in adolescents and be appointed by
109 the President Pro Tempore of the Senate and one of whom shall
110 specialize in early childhood and be appointed by the Speaker
111 of the House of Representatives.
112 d. One representative of the Alabama Department of
Page 4

d. One representative of the Alabama Department of
