113 Education.
114 e. Each of the following, appointed by the State
115 Superintendent of Education:
116 1. Two principals of public schools, including one
117 principal of an elementary school and one principal of a
118 middle school or high school.
119 2. One local superintendent of education.
120 3. One district instructional technology director.
121 4. One school curriculum and instruction specialist.
122 5. One local curriculum director.
123 (2) The appointing authorities shall assure the task
124 force membership is inclusive and reflects the racial, gender,
125 geographic, urban, rural, and economic diversity of the state.
126 (b) The task force shall provide recommendations to the
127 board on the screen-based instruction standards adopted
128 pursuant to Section 3. The duties of the task force are as
129 follows:
130 (1) Review up-to-date peer-reviewed research on screen
131 exposure and learning.
132 (2) Establish developmentally-appropriate grade-band
133 recommendations for screen-based instruction.
134 (3) Identify best practices to ensure technology
135 enhances rather than replaces direct instruction.
136 (4) Develop guidelines and best practices for virtual
137 delivery of instruction, including any e-days or remote
138 learning days.
139 (5) Issue written recommendations to the State Board of
140 Education no later than October 1, 2027.
