141 (6) Annually review its prior recommendations and, as
142 necessary, provide updated recommendations to the State Board
143 of Education for the next academic school year.
144 (c) The State Superintendent of Education and the State
145 Board of Education shall review any recommendations from the
146 task force. The board shall include the recommendations of the
147 task force in the standards created pursuant to Section 3.
148 Section 5. This act does not apply to any of the
149 following:
150 (1) Assistive technology required under an
151 Individualized Education Program (IEP) or Section 504 Plan.
152 (2) State or federally required assessments.
153 (3) A teacher's use of technology for instructional
154 displays or presentations.
155 (4) Temporary emergency remote instruction.
156 (5) Any computer science course or instruction in
157 computer science pursuant to Section 16-46B-2, Code of Alabama
158 1975.
159 Section 6. This act shall become effective on October
160 1, 2026.
